---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h4>üöÄ Git Workflows: From Development to Deployment</h4>
			<p>
				Welcome to our interactive workshop! This repository serves as a playground for learning 
				Git workflows, pull requests, and collaborative development. You'll contribute a blog post 
				about yourself and practice the complete Git workflow from development to deployment.
			</p>
			
			<h5>üìù Your Mission: Create a Blog Post</h5>
			<p>
				Follow these steps to contribute your introduction and practice the Git workflow:
			</p>

			<h5>Step 1: Fork & Clone</h5>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Star and Fork this <a href="https://github.com/<username>/iitm-git-workshop">repository</a></strong> to your GitHub account</li>
				<li><strong>Clone your fork</strong> to your local machine:
					<br><code>git clone git@github.com:ankitmhn/iitm-git-workshop.git</code>
				</li>
				<li><strong>Navigate to the project:</strong> <code>cd REPO-NAME</code></li>
			</ol>

			<h5>Step 2: Create Your Blog Post</h5>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Create a new markdown file</strong> in <code>src/content/blog/</code></li>
				<li><strong>Name the file using your roll number:</strong> <code>YOUR-ROLL-NUMBER.md</code>
					<br>Example: <code>24F100010.md</code>, <code>22DD100100</code>, etc.
				</li>
				<li><strong>Add the following frontmatter</strong> at the top of your file:</li>
			</ol>

			<pre><code>---
title: 'Introduction - [Your Full Name]'
description: 'Meet [Your Name] - Roll Number: [Your Roll Number]'
pubDate: '2024-11-10'
---</code></pre>

			<h5>Step 3: Write Your Introduction</h5>
			<p>Below the frontmatter, write a brief introduction including:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Your name and roll number</li>
				<li>Your branch/department</li>
				<li>Your interests and hobbies</li>
				<li>What you hope to learn from this Git workshop</li>
				<li>Any programming languages or technologies you're excited about</li>
			</ul>

			<h5>Step 4: Update the Participants List</h5>
			<p>Add yourself to the list of workshop participants:</p>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Open the file:</strong> <code>src/content/blog/common.md</code></li>
				<li><strong>Add your name and roll number</strong> to the participants list at the bottom</li>
				<li><strong>Format:</strong> <code>- [Your Full Name] ([Your Roll Number])</code></li>
			</ol>
			<p><strong>Example:</strong> <code>- Ankit Mohan (24F100100)</code></p>

			<h5>Step 5: Complete the Git Workflow</h5>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Add your file:</strong> <code>git add src/content/blog/YOUR-ROLL-NUMBER.md</code></li>
				<li><strong>Commit your changes:</strong> <code>git commit -m "feat: includes <roll_number> as participant"</code></li>
				<li><strong>Push to your fork:</strong> <code>git push origin main</code></li>
				<li><strong>Create a Pull Request</strong> from your fork to the original repository</li>
			</ol>

			<h5>ÔøΩ Example Blog Post Structure</h5>
			<pre><code>---
title: 'Introduction - Ankit Sharma'
description: 'Meet Ankit Sharma - Roll Number: CS21B001'
pubDate: '2024-11-10'
---

# Hello, I'm Ankit! üëã

